Comedian and event consultant Mc Morris has yanked off singer Portable from his upcoming event titled: “My hearing”. He shared this news via his Instagram story The event was slated to hold in Canada on May 22 with the Zazzu crooner expected to feature as one of the guest artists. MC said he excused Portable from the show due to the recent controversies surrounding the singer. He said it was not enough to have a talent, it was also pertinent to have a good attitude to back up the talent.   Sacked promoter cuts ties with Portable     Girl who touched singer Ruger inappropriately speaks out     Will Smith apologises to Chris Rock after Oscars slap   He complained that the singer has had one too many issues with people as he listed the number of people in an altercation with him. He apologized to the singer’s former promoter Ijoba Danku and further stated that he had written to the immigration services to deny the visa of the singer. He wrote: “For those asking why I removed Idamu Adugboyin from my May 22 show. Talent is not enough. A beautiful song without a beautiful attitude is beautiful nonsense. “Two managers in less than a year, even sacked the innocent DJ that his job was to play songs and scratch shaka shaka. “I cannot koshi mero, I’m sorry. All transactions cancelled and Ijoba Danku, I’m sorry, no one should use my invite please, I already wrote to Immigration to deny the visa.”